title: Moroccans
summary: Moroccans (Arabic: المغاربة‎, romanized: al-Maġāriba, Berber languages: ⵉⵎⵖⵕⴰⴱⵉⵢⵏ, romanized: Imɣṛabiyen) are a Maghrebi nation of mainly Arab and Berber descent[24] inhabiting or originating from the country of Morocco in North Africa and who share a common Moroccan culture and ancestry.
